"1": {"node_id": "Science-based ecosystem restoration for the 2020s and beyond", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/science-based-ecosystem-restoration-2020s-and-beyond", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "7f5c0716fa03f5d4e5462d2659754e77197b8660dcda2a68fd07e4b53f7889d0"}, "3": {"node_id": "e0cb8c2b-7239-475c-a2d2-622e213064d4", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/science-based-ecosystem-restoration-2020s-and-beyond", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "083b3ea145cc8bf7c449f87d0b2a61e14e21417ea826dc4fddeccddfbd9d1cb8"}}, "hash": "a73431bc295ae3800a898dd5c890c464d68d1b9b9fa6e757df4ba766e928e8b6", "text": "can work and the limitations of available knowledge. n Assess how ecosystem restoration fits with other development priorities and approaches (such as engineering solutions). n Identify social and economic benefits of restoration and the distribution of these benefits. Be clear about trade-offs and disbenefits of restoration. n Disseminate best scientific advice in readily understandable language. n Provide a service to interpret scientific findings and advice. n Undertake new research in priority areas that helps to design effective restoration actions and inform decision makers. Action for scientists and technical advisors n Find innovative ways to reduce risk in restoration investments and to increase opportunities, including by integrating natural accounting into investment decisions. n Develop social safeguards, due diligence, accountability frameworks, metrics and transparency. n Expand opportunities to integrate natural capital accounting into investment decisions. n Divest from companies and sectors that degrade ecosys